messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path
- /cms/user/information

Notes:
- The endpoint is defined as @user_api.route("/information") inside the user blueprint, which is mounted at /cms (cms blueprint) and the user blueprint itself is mounted at /user. Hence the full path is /cms/user/information.
- There are no path parameters in this endpoint, so no {param} placeholders are needed.

HTTP methods assessment (based on code)
- Are all HTTP methods acceptable? No (False)
  - The route decorator does not specify methods, so Flask defaults to GET only. It does not declare support for all methods.
- HEAD: Yes (True)
  - Flask automatically handles HEAD for routes that support GET. Since this endpoint supports GET by default, HEAD is automatically acceptable.
- POST: No (False)
  - No POST handling is defined for this route.
- OPTIONS: Yes (True)
  - Flask automatically handles OPTIONS for routes, returning appropriate allowed methods.
- TRACE: No (False)
  - TRACE is not defined or handled by this route.
- GET: Yes (True)
  - The route defaults to GET when methods arenâ€™t specified.
- PUT: No (False)
  - Not defined for this route.
- DELETE: No (False)
  - Not defined for this route.
- PATCH: No (False)
  - Not defined for this route.

Explanation
- The endpoint lives under the cms blueprint at /cms, then under the cms user sub-blueprint at /user, and finally at /information, yielding /cms/user/information.
- Because the route decorator does not specify methods, Flask uses GET by default. Therefore GET is allowed.
- Flask provides automatic handling for HEAD (for GET routes) and OPTIONS (for all routes), so HEAD and OPTIONS are considered acceptable even though not explicitly declared in the code.
- Other HTTP methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE) are not implemented for this route, so they are not acceptable per the code. Authentication requirements (login_required) exist, but the determination here focuses solely on HTTP method support per the code.
